annotationA: Xeroderma pigmentosum D is a DNA helicase that is a subunit of the basal transcription and DNA repair factor TFIIH
annotationB: RNA polymerase II 33kD subunit; DNA binding; protein dimerization activity; DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; cellular response to heat
